  "prompt": "How can I treat burning and dry lips?",
  "response": "Here are several ways to treat burning and dry lips:\n\n1. Hydration\n- Drink plenty of water\n- Use a lip balm with moisturizing ingredients\n- Apply petroleum jelly\n\n2. Lip balm ingredients to look for\n- Beeswax\n- Shea butter\n- Vitamin E\n- Coconut oil\n- Aloe vera\n\n3. Protection\n- Use lip balm with SPF\n- Avoid licking your lips\n- Use a humidifier in dry environments\n- Protect lips from harsh weather conditions\n\n4. Home remedies\n- Honey\n- Cucumber slices\n- Aloe vera gel\n- Coconut oil\n- Sugar scrub for gentle exfoliation\n\n5. Avoid irritants\n- Spicy or acidic foods\n- Harsh lip products\n- Flavored lip balms with potential allergens\n\n6. Medical treatments\n- Use hydrocortisone cream for inflammation\n- See a dermatologist if symptoms persist\n- Check for potential allergic reactions or underlying conditions\n\n7. Lifestyle changes\n- Stay hydrated\n- Eat a balanced diet\n- Use a humidifier\n- Avoid excessive sun exposure\n\nIf symptoms are severe or persistent, consult a healthcare professional.",
